  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed residential unit would provide substandard accommodation in the form of the poor provision of private amenity space, poor outlook from the main habitable areas at ground floor and insufficient information to demonstrate a suitable level of light to the new unit, contrary to Policy D6 (Housing quality and standards) of the London Plan (2021) and LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020)&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change)&amp;nbsp;of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed loss of Class E office floor space within a designated Priority Office Area (POA), Central Activity Zone (CAZ) and the Shoreditch Area Action Plan, would harm the vitality and function of the POA and CAZ, contrary to the NPPF(2021), Policies SD4(The Central Activities Zone), SD5 (Offices, other strategic functions and residential development in the CAZ) and E1 (Offices) of the London Plan (2021) and Policies LP26( Employment Land and Floorspace) and LP27(Protecting and Promoting Office Floorspace in the Borough) of Hackney’s Local Plan (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
